	</m:math>, which satisfies the slowly varying property.  We
	have verified Stein's Lemma prediction for the asymptotic
	behavior of the false-alarm probability in the Gaussian case.
	Note how the criterion value
	<m:math>
	  <m:ci>Œ±</m:ci>
	</m:math> occurs only in the expression for 
	<m:math>
	  <m:apply>
	    <m:ci type="fn">f</m:ci>
	    <m:ci>L</m:ci>
	  </m:apply>
	</m:math>, and hence does <emphasis>not</emphasis> affect the
	exponential rate; Stein's Lemma says this situation always
	occurs.
      </para>
    </example>
